(188, 'JSONderulo', 30184477, NULL, '2022-02-02 22:44:19', 'I noticed this too. Other day the restaurant slipped me a QR code in my bag to just go direct through them and save money. I checked and it&#x27;s about $1+ for each item on DD versus the restaurant.', 'comment', NULL, NULL, NULL, 30183341, 'None', NULL, NULL, 0),
(189, 'BobbyJo', 30184478, NULL, '2022-02-02 22:44:22', 'That&#x27;s not significantly different than how programming has worked for the last 40 years though. We slowly push certain types of decisions and tasks down into the tools we use, and what&#x27;s left over is what we call &#x27;programming&#x27;. It&#x27;s cool, no doubt, but as long as companies need to hire &#x27;prorammers&#x27;, then it&#x27;s not the huge thing we&#x27;re all looking out over the horizon waiting for.', 'comment', NULL, NULL, NULL, 30183031, 'None', NULL, NULL, 0),
(190, 'xwdv', 30184479, NULL, '2022-02-02 22:44:23', 'You can definitely trust comments on Hackernews more than other sources such as Reddit.', 'comment', NULL, NULL, NULL, 30154121, 'None', NULL, NULL, 0),
(191, 'rcarmo', 30184480, NULL, '2022-02-02 22:44:36', 'I wish I could use Garamond, but it’s not a “common” web font and its italics are dreadful, so I mostly adopted Georgia instead (with a fallback to whatever default serif the browser may have).', 'comment', NULL, NULL, NULL, 30180330, 'None', NULL, NULL, 0),
