(193, 'mrpadie', 30184482, NULL, '2022-02-02 22:44:40', 'We tried ReScript 2 years ago at work when it was still in its infancy, and still named ReasonML. Besides many other gripes at the time, one of the biggest pain points was the lack of any async&#x2F;await support, and a very cumbersome Promise wrapper.<p>Unfortunately, it looks like not much has changed[0], and you’re still forced into writing the equivalent of unwieldy Promise chains.<p>I ended up migrating us onto Typescript, which was a great move for us. The seamless interop with JavaScript combined with the massively active community makes it a no-brainer over other attempts at strongly-typed JS, IMO.<p>[0] <a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;rescript-lang.org&#x2F;docs&#x2F;manual&#x2F;latest&#x2F;promise\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;rescript-lang.org&#x2F;docs&#x2F;manual&#x2F;latest&#x2F;promise</a>', 'comment', NULL, NULL, NULL, 30181349, 'None', NULL, NULL, 0),
(194, 'throwaway4good', 30184483, NULL, '2022-02-02 22:44:42', 'Notice how much they are being hurt by apples ios policies. (Growth in revenue drops from 37 to 20 - corresponding to some 15 b pr year)<p>Tells you why Google is paying Apple and how much Apple potentially could extract.', 'comment', NULL, NULL, NULL, 30184344, 'None', NULL, NULL, 0),
(195, 'donsupreme', 30184484, NULL, '2022-02-02 22:44:44', 'FB went all in on Metaverse reminded me of Google between 2007-2012 when they mobilized the whole company around social with OpenSocial, Google Circle etc.  Google eventually realized that&#x27;s not their core strength and moved on, let&#x27;s see what will FB do.', 'comment', NULL, NULL, NULL, 30184104, 'None', NULL, NULL, 0);
