(269, 'FireBeyond', 30184558, NULL, '2022-02-02 22:50:35', 'Huh. Citation needed that drivers who buy, say, a Model S, particularly one with Ludicrous mode are less likely to be &quot;habitual speeders&quot; than the average driver.<p>This has come up before. When the new FSD beta started, people started claiming that safe driving was a function of vehicle price, and therefore Tesla drivers, especially those who had paid for FSD, were more likely to be safer. When I noted that my current vehicle costs more than a Model S, based on the logic, Tesla should be recruiting me to beta test FSD, well it was hard to find a refutation.', 'comment', NULL, NULL, NULL, 30183058, 'None', NULL, NULL, 0),
